			<div class="field-content"><a href="/neverwinter/neverwinter-is-getting-a-visit-from-minsc-and-boo"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://cdn.pcgamesn.com/sites/default/files/minsc%20and%20boo.jpg" width="594" height="334" alt="Neverwinter Elemental Evil" /></a></div>			<p>Neverwinter is a funny thing. A D&D themed action MMO, itâ€™s an odd blend of classic tabletop adventures, complete with Dungeon Master text, and hacking and slashing. It sort of works, though. Indeed, itâ€™s one of the more enjoyable MMOs when it comes to simply hitting things. I was thinking of a trip back in, but now I might hold off until the next expansion, Elemental Evil, drops next month.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The free-to-play MMO will be expanded with new areas, a storyline involving cultists getting up to no good throughout the Sword Coast, the paladin class and - most importantly - a cameo from a rather well known <a href="http://www.arcgames.com/en/games/neverwinter/news/detail/9068263-dev-blog%3A-minsc-%26-boo-in-neverwinter" target="_blank">hamster and ranger duo.</a></p>
